Installing Mongodb using brew
->Open terminal a) brew update
                b) brew install mongodb
                c) Check using type mongo
Using mongodb-
Before this let us first understand some basics of MongoDB-
In this each record is called as document,while group of records is called a table, it is called as collecctions in Mongo.

Some basics commands-
a) show dbs-to show the databases
b? use nameofdatabase-To allow the access to the database.

show dbs
db1
db2
db3

use db1;

show collections(tables);

db.nameofcollection.find();
It shows the documents(which is the rows of the tables)

db.nameofcollection.find().pretty();
Arranges it in a easily readable manner.


